40|$|Thanks {{are due to}} the <b>Asylum</b> <b>Support</b> Partnership One Stop Service {{staff who}} {{took the time to}} conduct the survey with clients – without their efforts this report would not have been possible. Thanks are also due to the many non-Partnership advice and support agencies, solicitors and campaigners who contributed {{evidence}} and expertise to the research. About the <b>Asylum</b> <b>Support</b> Partnership The <b>Asylum</b> <b>Support</b> Partnership (the Partnership) is a partnership of refugee agencies that are contracted by the UK Border Agency (UKBA) to deliver a range of services to asylum seekers, refused asylum seekers and refugees across the UK. The Partnership is made up of the Refugee Council (RC), Scottish Refugee Council (SRC), Welsh Refugee Council (WRC) and the North of England Refugee Service (NERS). The assistance provided by the One Stop Services (OSS) of the Partnership agencies includes advice on claiming <b>asylum</b> <b>support</b> and Section 4 support. 1 OSS caseworkers advise clients on their eligibility for Section 4 support, assist them to complete application forms and intervene with the UKBA to resolve delays or mistakes. This can also involve assisting clients to appeal a refusal at the First Tier Tribunal (<b>Asylum</b> <b>Support).</b> Structure of the repor...|$|R
