30|$|Importantly, {{from our}} perspective, {{the program was}} {{evaluated}} by the European <b>Asylum</b> <b>Support</b> Office (European <b>Asylum</b> <b>Support</b> Office, 2012). The evaluation report reveals important information about the conception and execution of the program. First, {{it is clear that}} substantial attention was paid to the selection criteria and demands emanating from participating countries, but candidate refugees’ preferences about destinations were largely neglected. This led to long delays, frictions and inefficiency.|$|R
